textRun.content: CMMI5: incorporou previsibilidade (Capability Maturity Model Integration)
Learning from success and failures from RUP + CMMI and first years of Agile + Lean, we got the following drivers:
The Software Architect is for the whole project, full time, with the team! (Pig and not chicken)*
No waste: only run processes and patterns which leads to agility and quality
Processes and templates needs to be detailed, customized and followed
Let's study responsibilities, processes and templates but what matters is the backlog delivered with quality and agility!
Clear responsibility of roles: What each one does?
Incremental architecture leads to faster deliveries: However, risk management and technical backlog must be more accurate, so critical tasks are not done incorrectly
Lean: eliminar desperdícios. Tudo tem que ser pensado na sustentação do projeto.
Agrega valor? Só consegue eliminar o que se conhece bem. Conheça o objetivo de cada prática.
Papéis e responsabilidades: nada pode ser muito “engessado”. Responsabilidades claras, mas customizáveis e combinadas para atingir o melhor resultado.
Evoluir incrementalmente a arquitetura, mas manter o mínimo para que o projeto comece. (RUP espera ter as definições para começar o projeto).
Muitas vezes não é necessário rodar exatamente a prática como ela é se o objetivo for atingido. Combinar as práticas para atingir o maior valor.
The process is organized into 20 practices!
that ensure architecture to be defined (or evaluated) and validated according to non-functional requirements of the system.
Environment & CIDeploymentTechnical Refinement & DesignArchitecture & Coding GuidanceQuality Assurance
Project Plan & RoadmapRisks & Blocks ManagementTechnical BacklogPeople & Technical Skills Development
Standards & Best Practices Discovery & DeploymentProcess Kaizen & DeploymentArchitecture Mgmt PDCAsCoach & Hire Systems ArchitectsTechnical Talents Mapping
Enterprise: práticas executadas pelos Gerentes de Arquitetura (formação e coaching de arquitetos e também auxiliar os próprios projetos).
3 perspectives which practices are from the contract
Software Architects do Arch. Management? Yes!
Mid-Level Architects only do Arch. Delivery? No!
System Architects do Architecture Definition? Yes!
Dependendo da complexidade do projeto, o próprio arquiteto de software pode fazer o management. É necessário para crescer.
The difference between Executor and Responsible
(on contrary of what many architects and managers may think)
Have a Developer that can make CI? Great!
Have an Technical SM that can make Technical Refinement? Great!
